&lt;p&gt;This fully functional installation of CMS Made Simple is ready to be built into anything you can imagine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are new to CMS Made Simple, the best place to start is with the &lt;a title=&quot;CMS Made Simple documentation site&quot; href=&quot;http://docs.cmsmadesimple.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;documentation&lt;/a&gt;. If you&apos;re ready to get your hands dirty, log in to the site admin console &lt;a title=&quot;CMSMS Demo Admin Panel&quot; href=&quot;admin&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; (or if this is not your site, go to yoursite.com/[path]/admin). Explore the templates provided. This page uses Simplex, which is sprinkled with comments and tips for modifying or building your own designs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you need further help, various support options are described &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cmsmadesimple.org/support/options/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;License&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CMS Made Simple is distributed under the &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; title=&quot;General Public License&quot; href=&quot;http://www.gnu.org/licenses/licenses.html#GPL&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;GPL&lt;/a&gt; license. This site doesn&apos;t need to publish a link back to CMSMS, as much as we would like such acknowledgement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some independently-developed add-on modules may have a different (compatible) license.&lt;/p&gt;
{News}

&lt;p&gt;CMS Made Simple is an open source Content Management System. It&amp;rsquo;s built using PHP and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Smarty&quot; href=&quot;http://www.smarty.net/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Smarty&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;template engine, which keep content, functionality, and display separate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;FOR EDITORS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At its most simple level, CMSMS is a system to help you keep a website updated through a comprehensive&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Content Manager&quot; href=&quot;https://docs.cmsmadesimple.org/content-2/content-manager&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Content Manager&lt;/a&gt;, which allows both editing and creation of new pages in real time, and a News module which allows the creation and control of article-based content such as news or blog posts. Supported by a&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;File Manager&quot; href=&quot;https://docs.cmsmadesimple.org/content-2/file-manager&quot;&gt;File Manager&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;for uploads and images, a&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Search Module&quot; href=&quot;https://docs.cmsmadesimple.org/tags/search&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;frontend&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Admin Search&quot; href=&quot;https://docs.cmsmadesimple.org/tags/admin-search&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;backend&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;Search Module, and a permissions-based&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Backend Users&quot; href=&quot;https://docs.cmsmadesimple.org/user-management/backend-users&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Backend Users&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;manager, CMSMS is extremely easy to use, making it a delight for non-technical content editors to manage the day-to-day running of a site.&lt;br /&gt;[&lt;a title=&quot;For Editors&quot; href=&quot;https://www.cmsmadesimple.org/why-cmsms/for-designers&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;More&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;FOR DESIGNERS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beyond content management, CMSMS is actually a powerful and customisable system that makes the perfect core for markedly more advanced sites and applications. For designers, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Smarty&quot; href=&quot;http://www.smarty.net/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Smarty&lt;/a&gt;-based templating engine means that there are virtually no restrictions on how the site can look. Unlike many other systems on the market, you will not be forced to shoehorn your design ideas into a pre-purchased template structure. Although there are commercial and free&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;CMSMS Themes Site&quot; href=&quot;https://themes.cmsmadesimple.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;themes&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;available, templating is so simple (with no need to know PHP!) that most designers find themselves adapting an existing design&amp;mdash;or building a new one from scratch&amp;mdash;in no time. The system lends itself to responsive design, and works extremely well with responsive frameworks such as&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Get Bootstrap&quot; href=&quot;http://getbootstrap.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Twitter Bootstrap&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Zurb Foundation&quot; href=&quot;http://foundation.zurb.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Zurb Foundation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;[&lt;a title=&quot;For Designers&quot; href=&quot;https://www.cmsmadesimple.org/why-cmsms/for-designers&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;More&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;FOR DEVELOPERS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CMS Made Simple&apos;s core provides for powerful expansion through the use of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Smarty&quot; href=&quot;http://www.smarty.net/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Smarty&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;templating engine, a robust module&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;CMSMS API&quot; href=&quot;http://www.cmsmadesimple.org/APIDOC2_0/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;API&lt;/a&gt;, and the ability to include your own PHP functions via&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;User Defined Tags&quot; href=&quot;https://docs.cmsmadesimple.org/tags/user-defined-tags&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;User Defined Tags&lt;/a&gt;. Combined, these provide the ability to make sites into powerful applications while keeping the content and design separate. You can choose between file or database templates (including template inheritance), complete control over caching, and a granular permissions system.&lt;br /&gt;[&lt;a title=&quot;For Developers&quot; href=&quot;https://www.cmsmadesimple.org/why-cmsms/for-developers&quot;&gt;More&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;FOR EVERYONE&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the above sections there is a vast array of powerful&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;CMSMS Modules&quot; href=&quot;http://dev.cmsmadesimple.org/project/list/module&quot;&gt;modules&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;created by the extended CMSMS community, many of which can be installed and ready to use at the click of a button within the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Module Manager&quot; href=&quot;https://docs.cmsmadesimple.org/modules/core/module-manager&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Module Manager&lt;/a&gt;. Adding a suite of modules, combining them with templates and core or user defined tags, rapidly allows for the creation of sites and applications with complex functionality without ever losing the simplicity of use for the website editor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can find out more about why CMSMS is ideal for your project&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;{cms_selflink href=&apos;why-use-cms-made-simple&apos;}&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A fast and efficient way to create stunning and sophisticated websites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;ADDING SITE CONTENT IS JUST A FEW CLICKS AWAY&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Content Manager makes content management simple. That&apos;s sort of our thing! Reorder site pages via drag and drop, and edit their contents with a click. All with no knowledge of HTML. Let the designers worry about the look, while the editors focus on content. Editing content is done with a simple editor with all the tools you&apos;ll recognize from word processors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;ANY DESIGN YOU CAN IMAGINE&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Join the growing number of design professionals who have discovered the foolproof elegance of CMS Made Simple.&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A question we often get asked is &quot;where are the templates?&quot; Although there are&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;CMSMS Themes Site&quot; href=&quot;https://themes.cmsmadesimple.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;themes&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;available, CMSMS was designed to eliminate the need to restrict yourself to premade or purchased templates. With some HTML and CSS knowledge, a developer can use Design Manager to put together a completely custom design in short order. With the inclusion of a responsive framework, it&apos;s even faster. Still want to use an existing design? No problem, CMSMS makes it easy to add your existing code: insert a few Smarty tags in key places, and you&apos;re off to the races. If you need a bit of help getting started, review the theme used for this page (Simplex) or one of the themes available on the &lt;a href=&quot;https://themes.cmsmadesimple.org&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;CMSMS Themes&lt;/a&gt; site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;EDIT SITE LAYOUT ON THE FLY&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using file or database templates, and a bit of &lt;a title=&quot;Smarty&quot; href=&quot;http://www.smarty.net/&quot;&gt;Smarty&lt;/a&gt; knowledge, developers have full control over layouts. Responsive sites, especially with frameworks, are simple (there it is again) to test and maintain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;EXTENDING A WEBSITE HAS NEVER BEEN MORE SIMPLE&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With a wide range of core and independently-developed&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;CMSMS Forge&quot; href=&quot;http://dev.cmsmadesimple.org/project/list/module&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;modules&lt;/a&gt;, a fully documented&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;CMSMS API&quot; href=&quot;http://www.cmsmadesimple.org/APIDOC2_0/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;API&lt;/a&gt;, the ability to include PHP code via&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;CMSMS Documentation Site - UDTs&quot; href=&quot;https://docs.cmsmadesimple.org/tags/user-defined-tags&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;User Defined Tags&lt;/a&gt;, and full&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Smarty&quot; href=&quot;http://www.smarty.net/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Smarty&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;template inheritance, there&apos;s no limit to the complexity you can include in the website. CMSMS is fully extensible, and is a perfect base for your applications.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CMS Made Simple&amp;trade; was first released in July 2004 as an open source (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-2.0.html&quot;&gt;GPL&lt;/a&gt;) package, which it remains to this day. That separation of content, function, and design has been a key ethic from day one and it&amp;rsquo;s why so many of our users stop looking for further solutions once they have found us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s not just our own user base that has given us such great support. CMS Made Simple has garnered a number of awards since its creation including runner up (twice) and winner of Pact Publishing&amp;rsquo;s &amp;lsquo;Best Overall Open Source Content Management System&amp;rsquo; in their annual Open Source Awards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since 2004, the core system has been regularly improved and updated with features, security releases, code improvements and much more. In that time, we have released countless new versions, each an improvement on the previous. In the summer of 2015, we released version 2.0, which was a nearly complete overhaul of the system. As we noticed our user base maturing to more advanced developers creating sites and applications, and larger design firms producing hundreds of CMSMS projects, it helped steer the project towards the powerful application base it is today with the 2.3 branch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The Development Team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CMSMS is developed by an international team of professionals who volunteer their time and efforts to design, develop, maintain, and market the system. In many cases this is in addition to running busy web and software development businesses themselves. Over the past years, many outstanding individuals have contributed their time and helped to shape the system that you can download today. You can find out more about the current Dev Team &lt;a title=&quot;CMSMS Dev Team&quot; href=&quot;https://www.cmsmadesimple.org/about/team/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;, as well as what they can offer through their own professional services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Development Team meets officially once a month, but remains in contact daily, collaborating within a defined organisational structure. The Dev Team is always delighted to hear from individuals who feel they have the resources and time to get involved. If you think you may be one such person, click &lt;a title=&quot;Join the CMSMS Dev Team&quot; href=&quot;https://www.cmsmadesimple.org/community/get-involved/develop/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; to find out more.&lt;/p&gt;
